sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: dCas 9
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: protein dCas9.Two mutations,D10A and H841A,from Cas9 gene without stop codon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Cas9 gene was got from Mr. Kai Tian,BGI Shenzhen China. The gene was splited into three parts to synthetize optimizing the codons in eucaryon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Protein dCas9 is the key of the technology CRISPRi,and this part is the gene of the dcas9.Delete its ending codon is to provide an convenient way to add other protein domain to improve the function of dCas9.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
To mutation four Restriction Enzyme cutting sites(SpeI) and two codons(D10A & H841A),we design PCR primers to mutate them by PCR using Phution DNA polymerase.
Refrence http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=repurposing+CRISPR+as+an+RNA-Guided+Platfrom
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shihong Chen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
